===Etymology===
[[File:Armistice celebration. Yanks and Tommies., 11-1918 - NARA - 530789.tif|thumb|A [[celebration]] of the armistice on 11 November 1918 that marked the end of [[World War I]]]]

From {{der|en|LL.|armistitium}}, from {{der|en|la|arma||arms, weapons}} + {{m|la|sistēre}} (from {{m|la|sistō||to halt, stand still}}, ultimately from {{der|en|ine-pro|*steh₂-||to stand up}}) + {{m|la|-ium||''suffix forming abstract nouns''}}. The word is cognate with {{cog|fr|armistice}},<ref>{{R:OED Online|part of speech=n|id=10864|date=June 2014}}</ref> {{cog|it|armistizio}}, {{cog|es|armisticio}}.

