{{en-noun}}

# A ([[short#Adjective|short]]) [[cessation]] of [[combat#Noun|combat]]; a [[ceasefire]], a [[truce]]. {{defdate|from late 17th c.}}
# A [[formal]] [[agreement]], especially between [[nation]]s, to [[end#Verb|end]] combat.
# ''Often in the form'' '''{{l|en|Armistice}}''': {{short for|Armistice Day||[[November]] 11, the [[anniversary]] of the [[signing#Noun|signing]] of the armistice agreement to end [[World War I]], [[commemorate|commemorating]] the [[fall]]en of that War}} {{defdate|from 1918}}
#* {{quote-web|title=Armistice Day: Macron and Merkel mark end of World War One|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-46165903|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181111065102/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-46165903|archivedate=11 November 2018|work={{w|BBC News}}|date=10 November 2018|passage=French President {{w|Emmanuel Macron}} and German Chancellor {{w|Angela Merkel}} have left their own mark of reconciliation at the start of events to mark the centenary of the end of World War One. They signed a book of remembrance in a railway carriage identical to the one in which the 1918 '''Armistice''' was sealed. {{...}} Mrs Merkel became the first German leader since World War Two to visit the forest near the town of Compiègne in northern France where the '''Armistice''' was signed.|lang=en}}

